FloatHead automatically causes a table heading to float at the top of the window once the user scrolls below its position.

This is similar to Scott Buckingham's floaty head (https://github.com/scottbuckingham/jquery.floatyHead), but was developed independently. (Not invented here syndrome :P)

Example usage:

<table id="foobar">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th>Some</th>
			<th>Example</th>
			<th>Headings</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td>This is</td>
			<td>Example</td>
			<td>Data</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>This is</td>
			<td>Example</td>
			<td>Data</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<script type="text/javascript" src="jquery.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript">
	$('#foobar').floatHead();
</script>